Let $$V$$ be a [[vector space|Vektorraum]] over a [[field|KÃ¶rper]] $$F.$$ The //projective space// of $$V$$ is the set $$P(V)$$ of one-dimensional [[subspaces|Untervektorraum]] of $$V.$$ If the dimension of $$V$$ is $$n+1$$ then the dimension of the projective space is (defined to be) $$n.$$

* If $$v\in V,\ v\ne 0,$$ then we write$$
[v]\coloneqq\operatorname{span}(v)\in P(V).
$$ The vector $$v$$ represents the subspace. If $$\lambda\ne 0,$$ then $$[\lambda v]=[v].$$

* We write $$P(F^{n+1})\eqqcolon FP^n.$$

